**Enhanced version with step size:**

```tsx
function EnhancedCounter() {
    const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
    const [step, setStep] = useState(1);

    const increment = () => {
        setCount(prev => prev + step);
    };

    const decrement = () => {
        setCount(prev => Math.max(0, prev - step));
    };

    const reset = () => {
        setCount(0);
    };

    return (
        <div className="counter">
            <h1>Enhanced Counter</h1>

            <div className="display">
                <h2>{count}</h2>
            </div>

            <div className="step-control">
                <label>Step size:</label>
                <input
                    type="number"
                    min="1"
                    value={step}
                    onChange={(e) => setStep(Number(e.target.value))}
                />
            </div>

            <div className="controls">
                <button onClick={decrement} disabled={count === 0}>
                    - {step}
                </button>
                <button onClick={reset}>Reset</button>
                <button onClick={increment}>+ {step}</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    );
}
```

**Key features:**

✅ Prevents negative values
✅ Disables decrement button at 0
✅ Uses functional updates for reliability
✅ Enhanced version supports custom step size
